Simple Sentences
Subject + Verb + Object: "Mi es un student" (I am a student).
Questions
Yes/No: Invert the subject and verb: "Es mi un student?" (Am I a student?)
WH-questions: Begin with the question word: "What": "Quid," "Who": "Qui," "Where": "Ubi," "When": "Quand," "Why": "Cur," "How": "Kum."
"Quid es ti?" (What are you?)
